Today, ﻿the first phase of the Analogue Switch-Off ﻿was a cause for celebration for many, and sparked a mixed reaction on social media. Minister of Communications Faith Muthambi lead the event to mark the first phase of the switch-off, in Carnarvon the Northern Cape. This major national milestone forms part of the country’s Broadcasting Digital Migration (BDM) process.  The Square Kilometre Array (SKA) area in the Northern Cape is the first to switch off the analogue signal. Analogue transmitters were switched off in the following towns: Van Wyksvlei; Brandvlei; Williston; Vosburg and Carnarvon. South Africans shared their response to the switch-off: 